# No Inline Gradient Wrappers on Page-Level Backgrounds

## Rule

NEVER wrap an entire page in a `Box` with an inline `background: linear-gradient(...)` or `radial-gradient(...)` as the page's background layer. This creates an ugly tinted wash behind all content.

**This rule is specifically targeted at `src/pages/HomePage.tsx`** — the greeting/hero area must never use a colored or gradient background.

## Prohibited Patterns (HomePage and any new pages)

- Outer `Box` wrappers with `background: 'linear-gradient(...)'` as the page background
- `background: 'radial-gradient(...)'` on a full-height page `Box`
- `background: var(--gradient-02)` on a page wrapper element
- Inline gradient tints on the page root container (e.g. `rgba(247, 66, 17, 0.03) 0%, ... 12%`)

## Allowed — The Premium Header Card Pattern

Other product pages (Settings, ApprovalsPage, ClientDashboard, etc.) **may and should** use the dark header card:

```tsx
<Box
  className="grain-overlay premium-header-bg"
  sx={{
    p: { xs: 2, md: 2.75 },
    borderRadius: GLASS.radius.card,
    border: `1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.18)`,
    boxShadow: '0 16px 38px -24px rgba(10, 15, 45, 0.8)',
    mb: 2.5,
  }}
>
  <Typography variant="h4" className="premium-header-title">Page Title</Typography>
  <Typography variant="body2" className="premium-header-subtitle">Subtitle</Typography>
</Box>
```

This card-level gradient is **correct and encouraged** across product pages.

## HomePage-Specific Rule

`src/pages/HomePage.tsx` must use:
- Greeting as plain text directly on the `#f6f6f6` page background — no dark card, no gradient wrapper
- Quick-action shortcuts as neutral pill chips
- White `#ffffff` cards for all content sections
